  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">TB LON APS: Alliance for Combating Tuberculosis In Bangladesh (ACTB)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">(Bangladesh):  The Alliance for Combating Tuberculosis in Bangladesh (ACTB) activity will contribute to the reduction of the burden of tuberculosis (TB) by supporting all forms of TB diagnosis, treatment, and prevention needs, and battling stigma and discrimination, by applying locally-derived solutions that tailor USAID&apos;s TB response to patients and communities.  This Activity will improve identification of TB cases, ensure access to quality patient-centered care for TB and drug-resistant TB, prevent transmission and disease progression, and strengthen TB information platforms through public and private sector channels.With FY 2020 funds, the Activity will increase case notification and improve treatment outcomes for all forms of tuberculosis by providing technical assistance to the Bangladesh National Tuberculosis Program (NTP) at the national and subnational levels.  The activity will support service delivery interventions to actively detect TB at an early stage; scale-up the provision of shorter treatment regimens and new drugs for drug-resistant TB; and, increase TB preventive therapy for people closely exposed to the disease.  The activity will work closely with the NTP, different divisions of the Ministry of Health and Family Welfare, and local government and municipalities to improve case detection, notification, diagnosis, and treatment in selected areas of Bangladesh.  Strengthening existing health systems, including private sector stakeholders, to combat TB among at-risk population will support Bangladesh&apos;s journey to self-reliance.The activity will support the U.S. National Security Strategy Pillar IV, the State-USAID Joint Strategic Plan Goal Two, and the U.S. government&apos;s mission objective of improved health status in Bangladesh.. .</narrative>
  </description>
